4:
Whoa! Another bomb flies straight
into the audience! The whole
stadium shakes in the aftershock!
5:
We know this game's a real
attention grabber, but keep your
eyes peeled, ladies and gents! Or
you might just lose your head!
9:
So this is the sport known as
ActFast... I'd heard the stories, but
doesn't this seem excessively
dangerous?
12:
Looks like it's pretty popular though.
It's pretty intense, and those ticket
prices can't be beat.
16:
As usual, the people here are after
the next big thing...
19:
Now that the ball's back in the field,
time to restart the match! Can Tri
Hurricane's Middy score a goal?!
22: All right, it's about time we finish this!
25:
Don't get cocky, Middy! I'm gonna
crush you this round!
28:
Oh my... That Middy girl seems to
know her way around the field...
30:
Uh-oh! Foreski's lobbed another
bomb into the audience!
43: A-a mutant?! You okay, little guy?
50:
And Middy comes in clutch with a
save for our unlucky spectator! A
fine and compassionate play
indeed!
52:
Ha! Playin' the hero now, Middy?
You're such a goody two-shoes... I
HATE that about you!
55:
Uh-oh! Better hold on tight, little
mutie!
59:
I-I'm not a mutant, I'm the Cha—
AHHH!
62:
She's done it! True to her nickname,
Whirlwind Middy rushes through the
field at breakneck speeds to score
the winning goal!
65:
You'd have to be faster than the
wind to catch me!
75:
There you are! I apologize for
making you worry. I am fine, thanks
to this young lady.
80:
Heya! You guys're Light's friends,
right? I heard all about you.
85:
And you must be Middy. Thanks for
saving Light back there.
90:
Don't sweat it. It was our match that
sent him flying in the first place. My
bad.
93:
I didn't know Light could float
around either. I probably did more
harm than good holding onto him
like that.
97:
No, with my current strength, I do
not think I would have made it out of
that field unscathed. I was incredibly
lucky to fall into your hands.
102:
Ahaha, well, I'm happy to hear it. But
I think I was the lucky one here.
106:
Once I had you in my hands, I didn't
get hit at all! The other team's shots
just whizzed by!
110:
You sure you aren't a lucky rabbit,
Light?
116:
N-no, your victory today was earned
by your skills on the field. Your plays
during that match were perfection.
121:
Nah, that wasn't anything special.
This was a pretty traditional match,
after all.
124:
If this had been a special match,
that play wouldn't have worked
nearly as well.
128:
Oh? Do they add obstacles and
such to the field during those
games?
133:
Sometimes. Other times they turn
the whole field into a forest, desert,
or even a huge pool of water!
137:
Wow, they can recreate all those
with virtual reality devices? Sounds
rough...
140:
It definitely takes some getting used
to. Training for those kinds of
matches is tough too. Replicating
those environments costs some
serious coin.
143:
If you happen to know any cheap
training facilities, let me know, okay?
148:
Actually, I think we might be able to
help you there.
152:
Indeed. Consider it thanks for saving
me.
162:
Wh-whoa, you even brought out the
welcome committee...
167: So, wait... Where the heck am I?
171:
This is Starview Village, a place
connected to a number of different
worlds.
175:
From here, you have access to any
number of worlds with their own
unique environments, including vast
deserts, lush forests, and a deep
blue sea.
180:
No way! This is perfect for my
training!
184:
Ah, but... Is it really okay for me to
know about this?
190:
Of course. Just don't tell anyone,
okay?
195:
You got it! My lips are sealed! I'll
even sign a contract if I have to!
200:
Hey, so how do we start this baby
up?! If I wanna go to the forest, what
do I do?
211:
Argh, I can't wait any longer! Come
on, let's go, Light!
